{
  "urgent": false
}

> {%
    client.global.set("lastAppointmentId", response.body.id);
%}

### =====================================================
### Calendar ICS – Happy paths
### =====================================================

### 10. Export calendar as downloadable .ics file – expect 200 with attachment header
### Should contain all 7 appointments across the week
GET {{baseUrl}}/calendar/me/export
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}

### 11. Subscribe to live calendar feed – expect 200 with inline header and no-cache
### Should contain the same 7 appointments
GET {{baseUrl}}/calendar/me/feed
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}

### =====================================================
### Calendar ICS – After cancellation
### =====================================================

### 12. Veteran cancels the Friday appointment
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/calendar/appointments/{{lastAppointmentId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}

### 13. Export after cancel – cancelled Friday appointment must NOT appear (6 events expected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/calendar/me/export
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}

### 14. Feed after cancel – cancelled Friday appointment must NOT appear (6 events expected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/calendar/me/feed
Authorization: Bearer {{veteranToken}}

### =====================================================
### Calendar ICS – Error cases
### =====================================================

### 15. Request export without token – expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/calendar/me/export

### 16. Request feed without token – expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/calendar/me/feed

